    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I am unsure there's an easy way to sort this out without creating a new API entry somewhere.\n\nBasically here are the possible cases:\n- html is served from http://www.example.com. OK\n- html is served from http://www.example.com/subfolder/. OK\n- html is served from http://www.example.com/subfolder/. Base href is /subfolder/. OK\n- html is served from http://www.example.com. Base href is /subfolder/ NOOK\n- html is served from http://www.example.com/subfolder/. Base href is /anotherfolder/ NOOK\n\nOK => everything works, links are the right ones\nNOOK => interface works, links are not the right ones. Since we have relative links by default, they will use the base href by default.\n\nOne solution to this, would be to provide an API entry like absoluteLinks: true in instantsearch.js.\n\nOR maybe we just need to preprend the current webpage url to the links, this would solve every cases I believe. What do you think @jpchaput?\n",
